{# Standard container healthcheck block.

   `test` is the image-specific probe (a plain string like
   'curl --fail -s http://localhost:80/ || exit 1', or a YAML flow-sequence like
   '["CMD", "wget", "--spider", "http://localhost:3000"]'). The timing fields
   default to the fleet-wide convention.

   The point of the macro is `start_period`: it is ALWAYS emitted (default 30s).
   With `recreate: always` (common/docker_deploy.yml) bouncing containers on every
   deploy and autoheal watching all containers (AUTOHEAL_CONTAINER_LABEL=all), a
   slow-booting service with no start_period fails its first few checks, is marked
   `unhealthy`, and gets restarted mid-boot — a needless loop. start_period gives
   the app a grace window before failures count.

   Bump start_period for slow starters (JVM apps, big TSDBs), e.g.
   pass start_period='90s'.

   Invoke at the service's 4-space indent so `healthcheck:` lands correctly:
       healthcheck('curl --fail -s http://localhost:80/ || exit 1')
#}
{% macro healthcheck(test, start_period='30s', interval=none, timeout='10s', retries=3, name='') -%}
{#- De-stagger the healthcheck herd: at a fixed 30s, the ~40 macro-using containers all
    started in the same post-reboot second probe in lockstep, firing ~40 exec checks
    every 30s. When the caller doesn't override `interval`, derive a deterministic 30-40s
    from a hash of `name ~ test`, so probes spread across an 11s window AND drift apart over
    time (different periods). Two services with a BYTE-IDENTICAL `test` string (e.g. grafana +
    littlelink both wget localhost:3000) would otherwise phase-lock on the same derived interval,
    defeating the spread — so pass `name=container_item.name` to break the tie. Callers passing
    `interval=` (e.g. the Pi's 60s) are untouched. -#}
{%- if interval is none -%}
{%- set interval = (30 + (((name ~ test) | hash('md5'))[:4] | int(0, 16) % 11)) ~ 's' -%}
{%- endif -%}
healthcheck:
      test: {{ test }}
      interval: {{ interval }}
      timeout: {{ timeout }}
      retries: {{ retries }}
      start_period: {{ start_period }}
{%- endmacro %}
